        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process for tour J09D:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09D_temp` from `decision_talbe` with all rows where `TOUR` starts with `\"J09D\"` and added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Classified each house:\n   - Counted distinct `EQUNR` per `HAUS`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA'` if a house has fewer than 3 equipment numbers.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'` otherwise.\n   - Overrides applied:\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1` between 500 and 599 → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`.\n3. Enriched data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` on `ANLAGE` ↔ `Installation`.\n   - Joined with `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR`.\n   - When both net and sales records existed, the exported customer fields come from `sales_master` (using `COALESCE` so sales overrides net).\n4. Exported the final result to a CSV named `J09D.csv` with exactly these columns and order:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n5. Sent the CSV to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the subject content as a process email (metadata stored in the session).\n6. Dropped the `J09D_temp` table to clean up.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also provide the exact SQL used for documentation or reuse.",
